- The integer result is the number of battleships on the board.
- Battleships can only be placed horizontally or vertically on the board.
- Battleships are represented by 'X' and empty cells are represented by '.'.
- Battleships are either in the shape of '1 x k' or 'k x 1', where k can be any size.
- At least one horizontal or vertical cell separates between two battleships.
- The method should be able to handle boards with dimensions up to 200x200.
- The method should count the battleships in one pass.
- The method should use only O(1) extra memory.
- The method should not modify the values in the board.